SIMPLE: inextricable
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Inextricable
<hw>In*ex"tri*ca*ble</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>inextricabilis</ets>: cf. F. <ets>inextricable</ets>. See
<er>In-</er> not, and <er>Extricate</er>.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>Incapable of being extricated, untied, or
disentangled; hopelessly intricate, confused, or obscure; <as>as, an
<ex>inextricable</ex> knot or difficulty; <ex>inextricable</ex>
confusion.</as></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Lost in the wild, <qex>inextricable</qex> maze.</q>
<rj><qau>Blackmore.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Inevitable.</def> <mark>[R.]</mark> ⟦ldquo⟧Fate
<xex>inextricable</xex>.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Milton.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><-- p. 758 --></p>

<p><ent>Inextricableness</ent>⟦br⟧
